parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_RADIO_UTILIZATION
parameters.description: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the uplink                                     direction using a 64-QAM modulation.  Successful is based on the CRC check, not based on if RBS sends                                     HARQ ACK (RBS can use the ACK even if the transport block was                                     not successfully decoded in a way to control the HARQ).

parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_RADIO_UTILIZATION
parameters.description: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the uplink                                     direction using a 64-QAM modulation.  Failure is based on the CRC check (which will result in an                                     NACK).

parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_RADIO_UTILIZATION
parameters.description: The total number of occasions when an uplink grant was meant for                                     HARQ transmission of a transport block using 64Q-AM modulation                                     in the uplink direction, where DTX is considered the reason for                                     no reception of HARQ in uplink in the eNodeB.

parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_RADIO_UTILIZATION
parameters.description: Number of samples for the measured SINR on PUSCH, with 17 <                                     SINR <= 20.

parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_RADIO_UTILIZATION
parameters.description: Number of samples for the measured SINR on PUSCH, with 20 <                                     SINR.
